  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational hemolysis study in which pump-induced blood trauma was measured across five clinically representative flow-speed operating points using donor blood samples from a certified blood bank. The study team recorded shear stress exposure histories, outlet hemoglobin release, and relative hemolysis index (RH) values under conditions closely matching the intended COU. The observational nature of the data collection — in which no experimental variables were independently manipulated by the investigators — provides rich real-world hemolysis measurements that directly inform the CFD model's predictive fidelity. The validation activity is cited throughout the credibility assessment as the primary empirical anchor for all output-comparison and model-form conclusions.",
