      "name": "CFD vs. observational hemolysis study — RH index comparison across 5 operating points",
      "description": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values from the CFD model were compared against measured RH values from the observational hemolysis study (Morrison et al., 2023). At all five flow-speed operating points, predicted RH values fell within ±12% of measured values, and the rank ordering of worst-case conditions was correctly reproduced. The observational dataset, collected from clinical-grade blood samples circulated through the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under standard CPB perfusion protocols, is considered representative of the COU. Agreement between CFD predictions and observational measurements supports the conclusion that the model achieves the required output-comparison credibility level.",
