    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The observational hemolysis study (Morrison et al., 2023) provides the primary empirical validation evidence, with predicted RH values agreeing within ±12% of measured values across all five COU operating points. The assessment team is satisfied that the validation evidence, combined with the mesh convergence analysis and software QA documentation, supports an Accepted credibility decision for submission to FDA.",
